40|$|Legal cases {{regarding}} student <b>on</b> student <b>sexual</b> <b>harassment</b> and Title IX are on {{the increase}} in both pre-K – 12 and college campuses. Case law related to student on student harassment policies in {{institutions of higher education}} remain unclear for the most part. This paper provides a summary of federal guidelines and a chronological review of case law. It also explores the current legal situation and institutional liability related to student <b>on</b> student <b>sexual</b> <b>harassment</b> <b>on</b> college campuses. It concludes by providing recommended steps that administrators should take to reduce liability in Title IX and <b>sexual</b> <b>harassment</b> cases. Title IX continues to be a heated topic of discussion on college and university campuses across the country. Usually the discussion surrounds the issue of athletics and institutions creating a fair playing field for women athletes and athletic programs. More recently, Title IX has become a concern for campus administrators with respect to sexual assault and <b>sexual</b> <b>harassment</b> issues. More than 59 % of college and university Title IX complaints involve sexual harassmen...|$|R
